The individual filling this position must be responsible, morally sound, clean and neat in appearance, prompt, have good attendance habits, and be able to get along with peers, supervisors, and the public in general.

For more information, visit our website at www.garaway.org/employment.aspx.

post_text: Welcome Mikayla Johnson, Intervention Specialist at Dundee Elementary. Mikayla is entering her fourth year of teaching. post_text: Garaway is happy to introduce Luke Warkall, who is excited to be starting his first year of teaching here at Garaway. Luke grew up in Sugarcreek and graduated this past Spring from the Baldwin Wallace University Conservatory of Music with a Bachelors of Music Education. He likes to read, play euphonium, go hiking, and attend concerts and musicals. Luke is really excited to teach music because elementary school students are so creative and imaginative, and music is a great place for them to explore and develop their own creativity! A fun fact about Luke is that he used to play the alphorn. Welcome back to Garaway Luke!

In the MENU click MORE and you will find all the forms. The same forms will be printed and available for pickup in the blue tub outside the main gym lobby doors starting Monday, June 1 if you’d rather pick up a packet. 1 packet per athlete. All paperwork and physicals must be completed by August 1 for athletes to participate.

post_text: One of our parents recently contacted us about a P-EBT (Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer) card they received in the mail for their students. After some research, here's what we found: The federal Families First Coronavirus Response Act of 2020 provides a temporary program called Pandemic-Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT). P-EBT provides children in kindergarten through twelfth grade eligible for free or reduced-price meals with Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP, formerly known as food stamps) benefits. The program is administered by the Ohio Department of Job and Family Services and the Department is partnering with the Ohio Department of Education (ODE) to ensure children and families receive this important benefit. Click the link to see more information and FAQs. https://jfs.ohio.gov/ofam/p-ebt.stm Our school has a high enough percentage of free and reduced meals, that all students may receive the benefits. *This is a government program independent of the school district.*

post_text:
We love our Pirates 💗 Congratulations Class of 2020!

"I know you are all well aware that you’re graduating in an unprecedented time because of the coronavirus crisis. But please understand, your future is as promising as it has ever been and I believe that you all know that you’re more than capable of working through whatever difficulties you may face. The measure of a person's character is often determined, in large part, by the way they handle the adverse situations they encounter. Life is full of ups and downs and unexpected twists and turns but don’t let these things distract you from the goals that you have set for yourself. Stay determined, stay focused on those goals, work hard, don't give up and especially don’t quit. Keep moving forward and see the good things that God has planned for you." ~Pastor Chuck Jarvis

post_text: Take out your telescope. Jon Gordon often talks about a telescope when encouraging people to create a big picture vision for their future and dream about the life they want to create. The telescope represents our dream for the future and according to Barbara Frederickson, research shows this is a simple way to boost positivity. Today dream about the life you want to create. Write down your big picture vision. What does it look like? What are you doing? What do you hope to accomplish? What difference do you want to make? What is your mission and purpose? Spend some time visualizing the future you want to create. Then write down your vision, dreams and goals. http://jongordon.com/files/1515/8316/5483/Stay_Positive_Action_Plan_WebRes.pdf

Celebrate the Success of your Day! Identify the one great thing about your day; the one great conversation, accomplishment, or win that you are most proud of. Or identify the one person you helped most today or the one thing that made you smile. Focus on your success, and you’ll look forward to creating more success tomorrow. Do this with your children as well so they can go to bed thinking and feeling like a champion and wake up thinking and feeling like a champion who is optimistic and ready to win.

They have a tower that utilizes wireless radios to deliver internet service which gives enhanced capabilities in rural areas when compared to the hardline providers. post_text: Garaway Schools will be closed tomorrow, February 7, in order to proactively provide our students time to rest and achieve optimal health during this cold and flu season. During this time and throughout the weekend, our custodial team will be completing thorough cleaning of all buildings and buses above and beyond the cleaning that has been performed daily. Thank you for your partnership in caring for our students. This day allows us to go beyond CDC recommended cleaning guidance by using our hospital grade equipment such as a disinfectant misting sprayer. This machine provides a no-touch application to environmental surfaces that can eliminate cross-contamination, and provide effective, efficient outcomes for the reduction in healthcare associated infections. This machine has been circulating throughout our district this season. Before students return to school, it will be used on all surfaces throughout the district again.

post_text: Today Mr. Joe Nicholas from Skool Dogs Inc. began addressing District staff and answered any questions they had about Sailor. Joe served in the United States Army 82nd Airborne Division where his passion for canines began. After his service in the United States Army, he became a Correction Officer for the New Jersey Department of Corrections. He proudly served as a Trainer and Canine Officer for the New Jersey Department of Corrections for 24 years-retiring in 2010. See link for a full bio of this passionate individual. https://www.skooldogs.scmediainc.com/team/joseph-nicholas-joe-nick/

post_text: Motivation Monday: Parker Wieland is a Garaway Difference Maker who raised $1,738 this summer to donate to the ALS Association. ALS is very close to Parker’s heart since his father passed away from the disease. He began finding glass at thrift stores to create flower plates. Big Brothers Big Sisters asked Parker to make a plate that would be sold during a live auction at their Gala. He was also asked to speak at the event about his project and how he creates his designs. His plate sold for $1,000 and Big Brothers Big Sisters split the profit from the plate between their organization and the ALS Association adding another $500 to his summer donation. If you would like to be a Difference Maker in the lives of those suffering from ALS and to support research to find a cure, the address is: ALS Association Northern Ohio Chapter, 6155 Rockside Road #403, Independence, Ohio 44131. Parker will be making more flowers this winter, if you would like to be added to the list to purchase one for $20, you may e-mail his mother at jwieland@garaway.org.
text: Motivation Monday: Parker Wieland is a Garaway Difference Maker who raised $1,738 this summer to donate to the ALS Association. ALS is very close to Parker’s heart since his father passed away from the disease. He began finding glass at thrift stores to create flower plates. Big Brothers Big Sisters asked Parker to make a plate that would be sold during a live auction at their Gala. He was also asked to speak at the event about his project and how he creates his designs. His plate sold for $1,000 and Big Brothers Big Sisters split the profit from the plate between their organization and the ALS Association adding another $500 to his summer donation. If you would like to be a Difference Maker in the lives of those suffering from ALS and to support research to find a cure, the address is: ALS Association Northern Ohio Chapter, 6155 Rockside Road #403, Independence, Ohio 44131. Parker will be making more flowers this winter, if you would like to be added to the list to purchase one for $20, you may e-mail his mother at jwieland@garaway.org.
